From 0b2c1cafc1b19e14b7144dc40f7a64d4603a974e Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Adam Williamson <awilliam@redhat.com>
Date: Tue, 14 Apr 2026 15:02:47 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] wifi: fix bogus addAndActivateConnection() arg from f801862

f801862 added this extra arg to the addAndActivateConnection()
call here which, AFAICT, is simply bogus. I'm fairly sure this is
the addAndActivateConnection() from plasma-nm Handler::Handler,
which takes exactly three arguments. The original commit seems
to have been trying to fix the connection to be system-wide(?),
but the commit message gives no indication why the author thought
this was the way to do it, and I'm pretty sure it's not.

I suspect this might be the cause of some of the "strange"
behavior Brandon Nielsen reported in
https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=2455469#c0 -
specifically "3. Password window disappears?" I suspect at that
point we hit this bogus call and the ConnectDialog crashed, or
something like that. The later steps probably wind up hitting the
not-broken addAndActivateConnection() call in main.qml ?

Signed-off-by: Adam Williamson <awilliam@redhat.com>
---
 modules/wifi/contents/ui/ConnectDialog.qml | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/modules/wifi/contents/ui/ConnectDialog.qml b/modules/wifi/contents/ui/ConnectDialog.qml
index 5baaa58..ac7992b 100644
--- a/modules/wifi/contents/ui/ConnectDialog.qml
+++ b/modules/wifi/contents/ui/ConnectDialog.qml
@@ -41,7 +41,7 @@ Components.MessageDialog {
     onAccepted: {
         if (passwordField.acceptableInput) {
             root.close();
-            root.handler.addAndActivateConnection(devicePath, specificPath, passwordField.text, PlasmaNM.Handler.StoreForAllUsers);
+            root.handler.addAndActivateConnection(devicePath, specificPath, passwordField.text);
         }
         passwordField.focus = false;
     }
